SUMMARY:MONTREAL: Plural Contemporary Art Fair + more   ( our 25th group t
 rip! )
DESCRIPTION:TORONTO ARTS & CULTURE\nThis trip is in 2 months. PLEASE read 
 everything over FIRST!!\n\nTo celebrate our **25th long weekend culture tr
 ip**--we return to Montreal...for 4 days. CULTURE CULTURE CULTURE\n\n## De
 tails:\n\n***After an 5-month break\, we will return to Montreal in Spring
  2026!!***\n\nOur 25th Group trip (2-3 trips each year since 2016).\n\nAND
 \, we will return to *PLURAL Contemporary Art Fair*--***-for the 8th time!
 ***\n\nCheck your calendars. All DETAILS are below.\n\n***(Note--this trip
  is filling up)***\n\n**PLEASE READ** **EVERYTHING** over before signing o
 n--everything you need to know is here. I'll try to make it work--but this
  trip is always in high demand.\n\n**There is a Non-Refundable fee to join
  us. Please Email me before signing up. All details are below. $150 per pe
 rson.**\n\n[https://www.plural.art/en](https://www.plural.art/en)\n\nCan y
 ou join us for a mid-April/Spring 2026 long weekend! We have the best time
  in Montreal!\n\nSomething to look forward to--as Toronto winter approache
 s. We normally post these trips 4-6 months in advance. This trip is in jus
 t 4 months.\n\n--Each trip is unique\, very organized\, individual\, and n
 ever to be repeated! For the culturally curious! Art/Food enthusiast. Expl
 orers!\n\nWe can work off a group size of 15 people.\n\n**VERY IMPORTANT**
 : Please read all the information before signing up to this trip\, as ther
 e is a **NON-refundable fee** involved upfront.\n\nCheck your schedules an
 d calendars--and then double check them.\n\n\\*\\*\\*Please do not sign up
  for the trip until you've emailed me. Very important.\n\nThese are very s
 ocial trips--we are 'explorers'. Montreal treats us very well. We generall
 y walk everywhere (thousands of steps!)\n\n**We will return to Plural Cont
 emporary Art Fair for the *8th time*.**\n\n[https://www.plural.art/en](htt
 ps://www.plural.art/en)\n\n**4 nights (Wednesday\, Thursday\, Friday\, Sat
 urday--returning home on Sunday)**\n\n**Plural** celebrates the best of co
 ntemporary art in Canada. Created *by* and *for* the galleries\, the fair 
 presents and brings together the plurality of voices and works in contempo
 rary art from across the country. It elevates art market practices through
  a rigorous selection of galleries presenting thoughtfully chosen artists 
 and artworks\; and through accessible programming that addresses current i
 ssues and questions in the field of art.\n\n**Plural's 19th edition** will
  be held from April 10-12th at the Port of Montreal’s Grand Quay. (Old M
 ontreal). Just a fabulous space/btw. Old warehouse.\n\nIf you are familiar
  with Art Toronto and The Artist Project\, then you have an idea about Pap
 ier Fair. **This is Quebec's most important Art Fair. 50 booths+**\n\n**Al
 so\, on the this trip**\, we will visit OTHER larger Montreal galleries an
 d explore various smaller galleries\, food\, public art\, and architecture
 . We will meet artists\, curators\, and directors--with private tours. PLU
 S more.\n\n--We spend most of **ONE** day at the Fair\, then the other tim
 e exploring Montreal's vibrant culture scene. After 20+ past trips\, we ar
 e so fortunate to have many Montreal culture/gallery friends--they look fo
 rward to us/and we to them.\n\nOur full schedule of events is not finalize
 d until late March 2026\, but I keep you posted along the way (every month
 ). **We meet as a group** before the trip in Toronto--mid/late March. TBD\
 n\nSpecial surprises always await us in Montreal!\n\n***Here is what you n
 eed to know to make a decision:***\n\n1. **I will** provide 3 1/2 days of 
 cultural programming **on the ground**. Wednesday night\, all day Thursday
 \, all day Friday and Saturday. You return home on Sunday at your own time
 .\n2. **You are** responsible for your own travel\, accommodation\, insura
 nce and other costs you will incur. In the past\, members have travelled e
 ither by air\, VIA\, drive\, Bus. They have stayed in hotels (points)\, Ai
 rbnb\, Bed & Breakfast\, Hostel\, or with friends.\n\nBy planning ahead\, 
 you can get the best rates etc. VIA and accommodations.\n\nThere is no "wr
 ong" place to stay in Montreal\, but ideally you want to be about 1km/20 m
 ins **walk** from St. Catherine St/Place des Arts.\n\n3\\. These are full 
 trips\\\, with very little "free\\-time"\\. We are on the go\\.\n4\\. On t
 he Saturday night\\\, we have a "full Group" restaurant dinner\\. About $1
 25\\-$150 per person range\\. This is the only formal meal event I organiz
 e\\\, although other meals fall into place while there\\.\n5\\. You would 
 need to be in Montreal and ready to go by about 6pm on Wednesday April 8th
 \\\, and you return home on your own time of choosing on Sunday April 13th
 \\.\n6\\. Can you attend\\\, please be sure\\.\\.\\.\n\n**There is a non-r
 efundable fee to participate in this trip\, and you MUST connect with me b
 efore signing up on Meetup at:**\n\ntorontoisculture@gmail.com\n\nThe non-
 refundable fee is **$150 per person** payable within 2 days of signing up 
 on Meetup.\n\n7\\. For your budgeting\\\, **other** gallery/event "entry" 
 costs may total $150 maximum over the weekend.\n8\\. By planning ahead\\\,
  you can get the best rates on travel and accommodations\\. **Be proactive
 . By doing so\, this covers your non-refundable fee. I travel by VIA\, and
  stay at Airbnb.**\n9\\. These are NOT expensive trips\\-\\-but they are v
 ery rewarding\\! Much of what we do while there is FREE\\.\n\nAny question
 s?\n\ntorontoisculture@gmail.com\n\nGreg
